oai_dc:dc.dc:title: CHANGE OF MEAN TIDAL PEAKS AND RANGE DUE TO ESTUARINE WATERWAY DEEPENING
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Niemeyer, Hanz D.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: tidal peak
tidal range
estuary
waterway deepening
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The deepening of estuarine waterways enforces essential changes of mean tidal water level peaks and range. Legal requirements ask for their determination by preservation of evidence. A method has been established to evaluate these effects quantitatively by statistical tools for each measure, even in the case of subsequent deepenings.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 26 (1998): Proceedings of 26th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Copenhagen, Denmark, 1998.
